headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers beat Wizards 102-93; Washington drops 9th in a row

events.name: Miami Heat at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen’s dunk with 2:01 remaining in overtime gave Cleveland a 100-99 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Saturday night, keeping the Cavaliers unbeaten in five OT games this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers beat Mavericks 100-99 in OT on Allen's slam

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 32 points and Damian Lillard added 25 as the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Houston Rockets 107-95 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons, Lillard lead Trail Blazers past Rockets 107-95

headlines.description: — Bobby Portis had 22 points and 14 rebounds starting in place of Giannis Antetokounmpo and the Milwaukee Bucks also played without Khris Middleton in a 123-97 victory over the Utah Jazz on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks beat Jazz without stars Antetokounmpo, Middleton

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Memphis star Ja Morant was ejected just before halftime and an undermanned Oklahoma City Thunder squad ended Memphis’ winning streak at seven with a 115-109 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies star Morant ejected, short-handed Thunder win

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Devin Booker dribbled toward the left corner 3-point line with two Pelicans in hot pursuit before rising up for an off-balance jumper. Coach Monty Williams wasn't sure that was a great idea.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 58 points, leads Suns to huge comeback win
